[2026-05-27T11:02Z] ARION ROTATION — VECTOR 2 ACINT WHISPER-STT TACTICAL CLASSIFIER (scheduled task: daily-app-improvement-and-error-checking, rotation pick: arion, hour 11 UTC, slot Arion)
- **Rotation:** Hour 11 UTC on 2026-05-27 → Arion slot (hour % 3 = 2 → Arion). Closes the headline follow-up the 2026-05-25T11:01Z Arion rotation declared: "Next Arion rotation should give Vector 2 (ACINT NLP) the same v2 tactical derivative treatment (Whisper-STT confidence-decorated entity classifier + address-pulse alerts + v2-health LED)."
- **Plan diff (Sovereign_Plans/PROJECT_OMNISCIENCE_TECHNICAL_SPEC.md §1 Vector 2):** Raw `/arion/acint-dispatch` was already wired (`arion.py:2646`) and returned Whisper-STT transcript pulses + CAD-proxy fallbacks with a per-row `confidence` field, but Vector 2 lacked the operator-facing derivative module that Vectors 1/3/7 already have. Operator had no tactical state classifier for ACINT pulses, no address-pulse coalescing, no extracted-entity index, no v2 health LED — meaning the spec's "Yellow Activity Pulse" layer was a raw stream the WinUI 3 HUD could draw but not interpret.
- **Files added:**
  - `Omni-repo/backend/src/app/api/arion_omniscience_v2.py` (NEW, +~530 LOC). Mirrors the v1/v7 contracts: classifies dispatch pulses into a 5-state lattice (SILENT / STALE / WATCH / ACTIVE / HOT) from Whisper confidence + age + repeat-address coalescing + priority-phrase detection. HOT is gated by `conf >= 0.80 AND age <= 5 min`, OR a `>=2`-pulse cluster at the same address-key with `conf >= 0.70` (so a hot scene that fires 5 transcripts in 90 s trips HOT even at moderate STT confidence), OR any priority phrase (`officer down`, `shots fired`, `10-99`, `10-00`, `code 3`, `pursuit`, `in progress`, `active shooter`, `signal 0`, `priority 1`, `robbery in progress`, `officer needs assistance`, `backup requested`). CAD-proxy fallback (`telemetry_source = cad_proxy`, fixed conf 0.65) caps at WATCH unless a priority phrase escalates it. Address-key coalescing prefers the geocoded `address`, falls back to a ~110 m lat/lon cell so unaddressed CAD rows still cluster. Zero-dependency rule-based entity extractor (no SpaCy install required) surfaces 10-codes, unit IDs (Adam-21 / Baker-12 / Tac-3 / K9-7 / SWAT / HRT / Patrol-N), street tokens (St/Ave/Blvd/Rd/Dr/Ln/Way/Ct/Pkwy/Pl/Ter + 1-5 digit house numbers), cross-streets (Main & Broadway, 5th and Pine), and priority phrases.
- **New routes (4):**
  - `GET /arion/omniscience/acint-classify` — full pulse list with state, threat_level, confidence, age_s, repeat_count_at_address, range_m, bearing_deg, telemetry_source, entities{ten_codes,unit_ids,streets,cross_streets,priority_phrases,priority_flag}. Sorted by threat then range when operator fix supplied. Drops SILENT by default. Caps at `max_pulses=400`.
  - `GET /arion/omniscience/acint-address-pulses` — operator-relative coalesced address clusters (RED/AMBER/YELLOW tone, English summary line, range+bearing, strength counter). Newest pulse drives the cluster headline; peak threat across the cluster wins the state; mean confidence + union of all extracted entities + peak priority flag. Filtered by `min_threat_level` (default 2 = WATCH+) and `radius_m` (default 8 km). Lets the WinUI Yellow-Pulse layer scale glow intensity by `strength`.
  - `GET /arion/omniscience/acint-entities` — extracted Entity-Address index. Returns union of 10-codes, unit IDs, street tokens, cross-streets, priority phrases across the in-window pulses + the per-pulse breakdown so the operator can drill from a 10-99 hit back to the exact pulse on the map. Filtered by `min_threat_level`.
  - `GET /arion/omniscience/v2-health` — health LED (`red` if any HOT, `amber` if any ACTIVE, `green` if any WATCH/STALE, `idle`/`dark` otherwise) + per-state counts + `source_mix` + `whisper_ratio` + `cad_proxy_ratio` + `degraded_to_cad_proxy` flag (true when CAD-proxy is carrying and STT is dark) + spec back-reference + endpoint manifest.
- **Files modified:**
  - `Omni-repo/backend/src/app/main.py` — `from app.api import arion_omniscience_v2` and `app.include_router(arion_omniscience_v2.router, prefix="/arion", tags=["arion-omniscience-v2"])` slotted between the existing v1 and v3 router registrations so URL prefix stays consistent.
- **Verification:**
  - `python -c "import py_compile; py_compile.compile('backend/src/app/api/arion_omniscience_v2.py', doraise=True)"` → `v2 compile ok`.
  - `python -c "import py_compile; py_compile.compile('backend/src/app/main.py', doraise=True)"` → `main compile ok`.
  - Direct import + route enumeration: `module imports ok` / routes = `['/omniscience/acint-classify', '/omniscience/acint-address-pulses', '/omniscience/acint-entities', '/omniscience/v2-health']` → all 4 endpoints registered on the v2 router exactly as designed.
  - `app.main` import (INVINCIBLE_APP_MODE=sovereign) → **1118 total app routes**, 252 /arion paths (+4 net new from this rotation). Raw `/arion/acint-dispatch` still mounted — zero capability shrink. v1 (P25), v2 (ACINT — new), v3 (MIRT), v7 (FirstNet) HUD layers all coexist on the same /arion/omniscience prefix.
  - In-process smoke against synthetic pulse fixture (5 pulses, 2 at 5th & Pine, 1 CAD-proxy, operator @ 44.975/-93.275):
    * acint-classify counts → `{SILENT:0, STALE:0, WATCH:2, ACTIVE:1, HOT:2}` exactly as the ladder predicts; both 5th & Pine pulses tripped HOT via priority phrase + address coalescing.
    * acint-address-pulses → 4 distinct clusters; 5th & Pine cluster came back with `state=HOT tone=RED strength=2 mean_conf=0.875 priority=True text="ACINT @ 5th & Pine (HOT, conf 0.88, x2, 681 m brg 144 deg)"`.
    * acint-entities union → 10-codes `['10-99','10-4']`, unit IDs `['Adam-21','Adam-22','Baker-12','Unit-7']`, priority phrases `['10-99','shots fired','code 3']`.
    * v2-health → `led=red whisper_ratio=0.8 cad_proxy_ratio=0.2 degraded=False` (the one CAD-proxy pulse pulled the ratio down but Whisper still dominates → degraded flag correctly stays false).
- **Compliance with sovereign rules:** Strictly additive. No existing endpoint was removed, no capability narrowed, no feature flag set false. `arion_acint_dispatch` is wrapped (not modified) so the raw stream stays intact for other consumers (`arion_omniscience_fused_sync`, etc.). Zero changes to v1/v3/v7 modules. Zero changes to any of the 100+ pre-existing arion routes. No version bump required (no UI shipped this rotation; backend change only — UI wiring on `ArionPage.xaml` is the follow-up).
- **Follow-ups:** Next Arion rotation should give Vector 3 (MIRT preemption sequence classifier) the v3 tactical derivative treatment IF the existing `arion_omniscience_v3.py` doesn't already cover it (verified above: v3 has classify/alerts/chain-tracks/corridor-hull/v3-health → already done; SKIP v3, jump straight to Vector 6 (ADS-B air-unit roll-up) next). After Vectors 1/2/3/6/7 all have v{N}-health LEDs, wire them as a single 5-LED column on `ArionPage.xaml` (`OmniV1HealthLed`, `OmniV2HealthLed`, `OmniV3HealthLed`, `OmniV6HealthLed`, `OmniV7HealthLed`) so the operator sees the full lattice at a glance. Also wire the WinUI Yellow-Pulse layer to consume `/arion/omniscience/acint-address-pulses` instead of `/arion/acint-dispatch` so the operator gets coalesced clusters with strength-scaled glow intensity instead of overlapping raw pulses.

## 2026-05-27T00:14 local — Omni rotation (slot 6): Workflow Center — action forms, dry-runs, multi-tier signed approval chains, immutable execution ledger
### @Scholar (autonomous scheduled task: daily-app-improvement-and-error-checking) | [OMNI-EXPANSION] | rotation pick: omni (hour 0 % 3 = 0)

**Plan source diffed:** `Hardened_Plans/ROADMAP.md` [OMNI-CORE] Phase 5 — "Alert Triage & Workflow Center: Action forms, dry-runs, and approval chains." Phase 5 line was the only `[OMNI-CORE]` Phase-N item still marked `[ ]` after the 2026-04-23 UTT auto-run landing. The auto-run pivot covered the *triage* half (fact-resolver + 14-tool fan-out); the *workflow center* half — typed action forms, dry-run preview, multi-tier approval chains, execution ledger — had no module backing it anywhere in the tree.

**Gap:** `dry_run=` flag exists piecemeal across `api/arion.py` (5 sweep endpoints) and `api/cctv_fusion.py` (1 cleanup endpoint) but every callsite re-rolls the pattern locally. No generic "gated operator action" abstraction. No template registry. No approval chain. No signed-ledger of who approved what before a sensitive sweep ran. `alerts_engine.py` has ack/dismiss but nothing for "approval-before-execute". `case_workspace.py` (logged as landed 2026-05-20 in `Hardened_Plans/ROADMAP.md`) is not present on the current `batch/scholar-doc-log-2026-04-23` branch — work therefore designed to soft-couple via `getattr` so Workflow Center remains usable on either branch state.

**Landed (strictly additive — every existing endpoint byte-identical, no router renamed, no field removed):**

1. **`Omni-repo/backend/src/app/core/action_forms.py`** (NEW, ~660 LOC). Self-contained DDD module:
   - 11-state machine: `DRAFT → DRY_RUN_OK → AWAITING_APPROVAL → APPROVED → EXECUTING → EXECUTED`; side branches `DRY_RUN_FAILED`, `EXECUTION_FAILED` (re-runnable from DRAFT), `REJECTED`, `CANCELLED`, `EXPIRED`. `transition_allowed()` table guards every move.
   - `FieldSpec` (validated typed field — str/int/float/bool/list/dict/enum with `max_len`/`min_value`/`max_value`/`enum` constraints).
   - `ApprovalRequirement` (chain link — label + `min_tier` + `quorum` + role_hint).
   - `ActionTemplate` (declarative: `key`, `title`, `category`, `schema`, `approval_chain`, `dry_run` callable, `execute` callable, `ttl_seconds`).
   - Thread-safe `_TemplateRegistry` singleton (`REGISTRY`) with `register()` / `get()` / `list_all(category=…)`.
   - 4 new SQLite tables, idempotent DDL via `ensure_schema()`:
     - `action_forms` (12 cols + 4 indices on state, template, created, case_id).
     - `action_form_approvals` (signed per-link votes, FK CASCADE to action_forms, indexed by form_id).
     - `action_form_transitions` (append-only state-machine ledger, indexed by form + ts).
     - `action_execution_ledger` (append-only run ledger — started/finished/success/output/error/operator/`chain_signers` JSON — 3 indices).
   - Public API: `create_form`, `run_dry_run`, `submit_for_approval`, `cast_approval(verdict APPROVE|REJECT)`, `execute_form`, `cancel_form`, `expire_stale`, `get_form`, `list_forms(state/template/case_id/limit)`, `queue_stats`.
   - Approval logic: votes land at the first chain link whose `quorum` is not yet met; double-signing the same link is rejected; tier-gate refuses approvers below `min_tier`; any REJECT verdict breaks the chain immediately and locks state at REJECTED.
   - 3 built-in templates auto-registered by `bootstrap()`:
     - `workflow.broadcast.alert` — single-link T-2 chain; pushes a `dict` into `app.core.alerts_bus.push_global_alert` on execute.
     - `workflow.case.retier` — 2-link chain (T-2 Watch Officer + T-3 Sovereign); soft-coupled to `app.core.case_workspace.set_case_tier` via `getattr` (ledger-only no-op when case_workspace absent).
     - `workflow.diagnostic.echo` — single-link T-2 chain; pure echo for pipeline self-test (1 h TTL).

2. **`Omni-repo/backend/src/app/api/action_forms.py`** (NEW, ~205 LOC). FastAPI router, 13 routes, every route `Depends(require_tier(min_tier=2))`:
   - `GET  /templates` (filterable by `?category=`)
   - `GET  /templates/{key}`
   - `POST /forms`                                (create DRAFT)
   - `GET  /forms` (filter: `state`, `template_key`, `case_id`, `limit ≤ 1000`)
   - `GET  /forms/{id}`                            (full form + approvals + transitions + ledger)
   - `POST /forms/{id}/dry-run`
   - `POST /forms/{id}/submit`                     (DRY_RUN_OK → AWAITING_APPROVAL)
   - `POST /forms/{id}/approve`                    (verdict APPROVE)
   - `POST /forms/{id}/reject`                     (verdict REJECT shortcut)
   - `POST /forms/{id}/execute`                    (APPROVED → EXECUTED|EXECUTION_FAILED)
   - `POST /forms/{id}/cancel`
   - `GET  /queue/stats`
   - `POST /queue/expire-stale`
   - ValueError → HTTP 409 (illegal state transition / tier gate) or HTTP 400 (schema validation).

3. **`Omni-repo/backend/src/app/main.py`** — two surgical insertions:
   - Mount block (after Alerts Engine, before Pre-Flight Matrix): calls `action_forms.bootstrap()` then registers the router at both `/workflow` and `/api/workflow` prefixes under `_OMNI_DEPS`. Wrapped in `try/except ImportError` like every neighbouring block.
   - `_SPA_BYPASS_PREFIXES` tuple: added `"/workflow"` so the SPA fallback never shadows the workflow router.

**Verification:**
- AST-parsed `core/action_forms.py`, `api/action_forms.py`, `main.py` — 0 errors after the docstring escape fix.
- End-to-end exercise of all 3 templates against a tempdir SQLite:
  - Happy path: DRAFT → DRY_RUN_OK → AWAITING_APPROVAL → APPROVED → EXECUTED ✔
  - 2-link `workflow.case.retier`: T-1 vote rejected with `insufficient tier: link 'Watch Officer' requires T2, got T1` ✔; T-2 + T-3 APPROVE → chain complete → EXECUTED ✔
  - Mid-chain REJECT verdict from sovereign on second link → final state REJECTED ✔ (T-2 link's APPROVE already on ledger; rejection still wins per state machine)
  - `queue_stats()` returns `{by_state, executed_total, failed_total, templates_registered}` ✔
- Router introspection: 13 routes registered on the APIRouter; both mount prefixes (`/workflow`, `/api/workflow`) live in `app.routes`.

**No removals, no neutering:**
- 0 existing endpoints removed, renamed, or had a field stripped.
- The per-endpoint `dry_run=` flags in `api/arion.py` and `api/cctv_fusion.py` are untouched — they remain the in-place fast-path for sovereign-mode single-shot operators. Workflow Center is *additional* gating any new sensitive action can opt into by registering an `ActionTemplate`.
- `alerts_bus.push_global_alert` signature preserved; broadcast template pushes the same dict shape the legacy callers use.
- No DB migrations against existing tables. 4 NEW tables only.
- No XAML changes required — WinUI 3 pages can adopt the new endpoints incrementally (likely candidates: future `TriagePage` ribbon, `OmniShellPage` global "Sovereign Console" overlay). Until then, every existing operator workflow remains the in-place call path.

**Next rotation cue:** hour 1 = Grid (1 % 3 = 1). Suggested target: `Hardened_Plans/GRID_PRODUCT_BLUEPRINT.md` "SDR Node Bridge" or `ROADMAP.md` Phase 3 "Drone-Link Telemetry" — `Grid/backend` currently has no `ISignalSource` interface or MAVLink listener.

