- **Plan source:** Grid/GRID_PLAN_BOOK.md Ch.8 "Identity, Auth, Credential Vault" + Ch.57 "Credential Vault" + Ch.9.5 "Universal Zero-Touch Provisioning (Universal ZTP)". The grid2 namespace had discovery + drivers + intent + autosetup + drift + apply (commit-confirmed engine landed last hour at 167 routes) but **the apply engine had no credential layer and no ZTP responder** — dispatch went to stub transports because there was no way to bind real per-device secrets, and there was no zero-touch flow for brownfield/greenfield device adoption.
- **Vault package — `Grid/backend/src/app/grid2/vault/` (6 modules, ~1080 LOC):**
  * `credential.py` — `Credential` dataclass with 7-member `SecretType` enum (PASSWORD/ENABLE_SECRET/SSH_KEYPAIR/API_TOKEN/SNMPV3/PSK/CERT_PRIVKEY), MAC canonicalization (strip separators, lowercase) so `AA:BB:CC:11:22:33` and `aabbcc-112233` resolve to the same vault slot, deterministic `vault_id = sha256(device_id|secret_type|username)[:32]`, `to_dict_redacted()` for safe-to-log shape.
