  4-state machine PENDING -> IN_FLIGHT -> DRAINED|DEAD with bounded
  attempt count (8) and exponential backoff ladder (0s/1s/5s/15s/60s/
  300s/900s/3600s).  Optional dedupe_key for idempotency.  Janitor compacts
  DRAINED rows > 24h and DEAD rows > 30d.  Max payload 64 KiB per op.
- backend/src/app/core/local_cache_policy.py       (~373 LOC) — tiered
  RAM+SQLite cache with 4 retention classes: EPHEMERAL (8 MiB,
  process-local), SESSION (32 MiB), DURABLE (256 MiB, survives restart),
  SOVEREIGN (64 MiB, write-locked once `sealed=True` until operator
  unseals).  LRU eviction per tier, TTL expiry tick, max 4 MiB / entry.
- backend/src/app/core/reconnect_orchestrator.py   (~402 LOC) — drives
  LIVE / DEGRADED / OFFLINE link state from registered ProbeCallables
  (1 failure -> DEGRADED, 3+ consecutive -> OFFLINE).  On drain cycle,
  pulls due ops from offline_queue and routes them to registered
  DrainCallable handlers keyed by op_kind.  Persists every state
  transition + every drain attempt to reconnect_events for the HUD.
  Ships with a default `catalog.freshness` probe that ties into Phase-6
  source_catalog overall_summary().
- backend/src/app/api/offline_modes.py             (~224 LOC) — 16 distinct
  endpoints (18 method-paths due to GET/PUT/DELETE on /cache/{ns}/{key})
  under /api/offline-modes/, all behind _OMNI_DEPS (require_tier>=2):
    GET    /summary                        Phase-7 dashboard rollup
    GET    /link/state                     current link state + uptime
    POST   /link/probe                     run probes now
    GET    /link/probes                    probe roster + streaks
    GET    /queue                          list ops by state
    GET    /queue/{queue_id}               op detail
    POST   /queue/enqueue                  operator / agent push
    POST   /queue/{queue_id}/requeue       DEAD -> PENDING (operator)
    POST   /queue/drain                    force drain cycle
    POST   /queue/compact                  janitor pass
    GET    /cache                          list entries (ns/tier filter)
    GET    /cache/summary                  per-tier rollup
    POST   /cache/expire-tick              drop expired now
    GET    /cache/{namespace}/{key}        single entry + payload
    PUT    /cache/{namespace}/{key}        put entry (tier/ttl/seal)
    DELETE /cache/{namespace}/{key}        delete entry
    POST   /cache/{namespace}/{key}/unseal unseal SOVEREIGN row
    GET    /events                         recent reconnect events

New DB tables (all CREATE IF NOT EXISTS, zero migration risk):
- offline_queued_ops      (PK queue_id, 12 cols, 4 indexes including
                           partial index on dedupe_key)
- local_cache_entries     (PK namespace+key, 10 cols, 3 indexes
